": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}], "identifier": [{"result": {"value": "knitcitations", "type": "String"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}], "readme_url": [{"result": {"value": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md", "type": "String"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}, {"result": {"value": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/README.md", "type": "Url"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "file_exploration"}], "authors": [{"result": {"value": "Carl Boettiger", "type": "String", "email": "cboettig@gmail.com", "identifier": "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1642-628X"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}], "requirements": [{"result": {"value": "RefManageR==0.8.2", "name": "RefManageR", "version": "0.8.2", "type": "Software_application"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}, {"result": {"value": "digest", "name": "digest", "type": "Software_application"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}, {"result": {"value": "httr==0.3", "name": "httr", "version": "0.3", "type": "Software_application"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}, {"result": {"value": "methods", "name": "methods", "type": "Software_application"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}, {"result": {"value": "utils", "name": "utils", "type": "Software_application"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}, {"result": {"value": "R==3.0", "name": "R", "version": "3.0", "type": "Software_application"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cboettig/knitcitations/master/codemeta.json"}], "installation": [{"result": {"value": "Install the development version directly from Github \n\n```r\nlibrary(devtools)\ninstall_github(\"cboettig/knitcitations\")\n```\n\nOr install the current release from your CRAN mirror with `install.packages(\"knitcitations\")`.  \n\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Installation", "parent_header": ["knitcitations"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}], "usage": [{"result": {"value": "Start by loading the library.  It is usually good to also clear the bibliographic environment after loading the library, in case any citations are already stored there:  \n\n\n```r\nlibrary(\"knitcitations\")\ncleanbib()\n```\n\nSet pandoc as the default format:\n\n\n```r\noptions(\"citation_format\" = \"pandoc\")\n```\n\n(Note: The old method will eventually be deprecated.  For documents using `knitcitations <= 0.5` it will become necessary to set this as `\"compatibility\"`).  \n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Quick start: rmarkdown (pandoc) mode", "parent_header": ["knitcitations"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}, {"result": {"value": "When the citation is called, a key in the format `FirstAuthorsLastName_Year` is automatically created for this citation, so we can now continue to cite this article without remembering the DOI, using the command `citep(\"Abrams_2012\")` creates the citation [@Abrams_2012] without mistaking it for a new article.  \n\n\n\n\n\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Re-using Keys", "parent_header": ["knitcitations", "Quick start: rmarkdown (pandoc) mode"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}, {"result": {"value": "At the end of the document, include a chunk containing the command:\n\n\n```r\nwrite.bibtex(file=\"references.bib\")\n```\n\nUse the chunk options `echo=FALSE` and `message=FALSE` to hide the chunk command and output.  \n\nThis creates a Bibtex file with the name given.  [Pandoc](https://johnmacfarlane.net/pandoc) can then be used to compile the markdown into HTML, MS Word, LaTeX, PDF, or many other formats, each with the desired journal styling. Pandoc is now integrated with [RStudio](https://rstudio.com) through the [rmarkdown](https://rmarkdown.rstudio.com/) package.  Pandoc appends these references to the end of the markdown document automatically.  In this example, we have added a yaml header to our Rmd file which indicates the name of the bib file being used, and the optional link to a [CSL](https://github.com/citation-style-language/styles) stylesheet which formats the output for the ESA journals:\n\n```yaml\n---\nbibliography: \"references.bib\"\ncsl: \"ecology.csl\"\noutput:\n  html_document\n---\n```\n\n\nThen calling `rmarkdown::render(\"intro.Rmd\")` from R on the tutorial compiles the output markdown, with references in the format of the ESA journals.  \n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Displaying the final bibliography", "parent_header": ["knitcitations", "Quick start: rmarkdown (pandoc) mode"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}], "citation": [{"result": {"value": "Cite an article by DOI and the full citation information is gathered automatically. By default this now generates a citation in pandoc-flavored-markdown format. We use the inline command `citep(\"10.1890/11-0011.1\")` to create this citation [@Abrams_2012].  \n\nAn in-text citation is generated with `citet`, such as `citet(\"10.1098/rspb.2013.1372\")` creating the citation to @Boettiger_2013.  \n\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Cite by DOI", "parent_header": ["knitcitations", "Quick start: rmarkdown (pandoc) mode"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}, {"result": {"value": "Not all the literature we may wish to cite includes DOIs, such as [arXiv](https://arxiv.org/) preprints, Wikipedia pages, or other academic blogs.  Even when a DOI is present it is not always trivial to locate.  With version 0.4-0, `knitcitations` can produce citations given any URL using the [Greycite API](http://greycite.knowledgeblog.org). For instance, we can use the call `citep(\"http://knowledgeblog.org/greycite\")` to generate the citation to the Greycite tool [@greycite2739].  \n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Cite by URL", "parent_header": ["knitcitations", "Quick start: rmarkdown (pandoc) mode"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}, {"result": {"value": "We can also use `bibentry` objects such as R provides for citing packages (using R's `citation()` function): `citep(citation(\"knitr\")` produces [@Xie_2014; @Xie_2013; @Xie_2014a].  Note that this package includes citations to three objects, and pandoc correctly avoids duplicating the author names.  In pandoc mode, we can still use traditional pandoc-markdown citations like `@Boettiger2013` which will render as @Boettiger2013 without any R code, provided the citation is already in the `.bib` file we name (see below).\n\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Cite bibtex and bibentry objects directly", "parent_header": ["knitcitations", "Quick start: rmarkdown (pandoc) mode"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}, {"result": {"value": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "References"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}], "repository_status": [{"result": {"type": "Url", "value": "https://www.repostatus.org/#inactive", "description": "Inactive \u2013 The project has reached a stable, usable state but is no longer being actively developed; support/maintenance will be provided as time allows."}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "regular_expression", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}], "related_papers": [{"result": {"type": "Url", "value": "https://arxiv.org/"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "regular_expression", "source": "https://github.com/cboettig/knitcitations/blob/master/README.md"}]}